Name: pyhdf
Version: 0.7-3
Author: Andre Gosselin
Author-email: Andre.Gosselin@dfo-mpo.gc.ca
Maintainer: Enthought Inc.
Maintainer-email: enthought-dev@mail.enthought.com
Home-page: www.sourceforge.net/projects/pysclint
Download-url: www.sourceforge.net/projects/pysclint
Summary: Python interface to the NCSA HDF4 library
License: public
Description: The pyhdf package wraps the functionality
of the NCSA HDF4 library inside a Python OOP
framework. The SD (scientific dataset), VS
(Vdata) and V (Vgroup) APIs are currently implemented.
SD datasets are read/written through numpy arrays. 
netCDF files can also be read and modified with pyhdf.
Keywords: hdf,netcdf,numpy,python
Platform: unix, linux
